According to the lease agreement between Union Pacific Railroad Company (Lessor) and CXT Incorporated (Lessee), the Lessee is not allowed to sublease the premises without the prior consent of the Lessor. Section 18 of the lease explicitly states that the Lessee shall not sublease the Premises, in whole or in part, or assign, encumber, or transfer this Lease without the prior consent of the Lessor, which may be denied at the Lessor's sole and absolute discretion. Any purported transfer or assignment without the Lessor's consent shall be void and considered a default by the Lessee.
A. Lessee shall not sublease the Premises, in whole or in part, or assign, encumber or transfer (by operation of law or otherwise) this Lease, without the prior consent of Lessor, which consent may be denied at Lessor’s sole and absolute discretion. Any purported transfer or assignment without Lessor’s consent shall be void and shall be a default by Lessee.